SIMPLE: suspensive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suspensive
<hw>Sus*pen"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>suspensif</ets>. See <er>Suspend</er>.]</ety> <def>Tending to
suspend, or to keep in suspense; causing interruption or delay;
uncertain; doubtful.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In <xex>suspensive</xex>
thoughts.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Beaumont.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>suspensive</xex>
veto.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The provisional and <qex>suspensive</qex> attitude.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Morley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Suspensive</b></col><cd> condition <fld>(Scots
Law)</fld>, a condition precedent, or a condition without the
performance of which the contract can not be completed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspensor</ent>⟦br⟧
